message.entry: Operation mode must be specified by a character string.
Unknown operation mode.
The equalized message is the only output allowed for Reset operation mode.
Only numeric arguments are allowed for the optional inputs.
Invalid syntax. Too many input arguments.
Samples per input symbol must be a positive integer scalar.
Channel coefficients must be a vector whose length is a multiple of the Samples per symbol parameter.
Seven input arguments have been provided. This is not allowed. Specify both preamble and postamble. If one of them does not exist, use empty matrix.
Seven input arguments have been provided. This is not allowed in the Continuous operation mode.
Eight input arguments have been provided. This is only allowed for the Reset\noperation mode.
Nine input arguments have been provided. This is only allowed for the Continuous\noperation mode.
Input signal X must be a vector of complex numbers.
Length of the input signal vector X must be a multiple of the number of samples per input symbol output symbol.
Input signal X must be a vector of complex numbers.
Complex constellation points must be a vector of at least two elements.
Traceback depth must be a positive integer scalar.
For the Reset mode, traceback depth must be a positive integer scalar not\nlarger than the number of input symbols.
When using [] as the default for INIT_METRIC, INIT_STATES and INIT_INPUTS must\nalso be [].

The initial state metrics must be a real vector with length equal to the number\nof states, where numStates = M^(L-1), where M is the order of modulation and L is\nthe length of the channel''s impulse response in symbols.
When using [] as the default for INIT_STATES, INIT_METRIC and INIT_INPUTS must\nalso be [].

The initial traceback state must be a matrix of integers between 0 
and (numStates-1), where numStates = M^(L-1), M = order of modulation,
and L = length of channel''s impulse response in symbols.
The matrix must have numStates rows and TBLEN columns.
When using [] as the default for INIT_INPUTS, INIT_METRIC and INIT_STATES must\nalso be [].

The initial traceback input must be a matrix of integers between 0 
and (numStates-1), where numStates = M^(L-1), M = order of modulation,
and L = length of channel''s impulse response in symbols.
The matrix must have numStates rows and TBLEN columns.
